# Example of a multiplex node (super node) with links to hubs and high-degree nodes
<https://example.com/SuperNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/SuperNodeLoad> ;
  noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkLeadership> .

<https://example.com/HubNode1> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOperationsTeam> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode1> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOperationsTeam> .

<https://example.com/HubNode2> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/EdgeTeam> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode2> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode3> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/RegionalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode3> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode4> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/LocalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode4> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode5> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/RegionalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode5> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode6> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/LocalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode6> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode7> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/RegionalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode7> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode8> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/LocalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode8> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode9> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/RegionalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode9> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

<https://example.com/HubNode10> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/LocalOps> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode10> noria:elementManagedBy <https://example.com/NetworkOps> .

# Link nodes to each other to form a network graph
<https://example.com/HubNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/HubLoad1> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/RouterLoad1> .
<https://example.com/CentralNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/ServerLoad1> .
<https://example.com/ConnectorNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/FirewallStatus1> .
<https://example.com/IntermediaryNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/TrafficStatus1> .
<https://example.com/MuxNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/DataMux1> .
<https://example.com/SuperNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/SuperLoad1> .

# Connect nodes via relations
<https://example.com/HubNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/HubLoad1> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/RouterLoad1> .
<https://example.com/CentralNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/ServerLoad1> .
<https://example.com/ConnectorNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/FirewallStatus1> .
<https://example.com/IntermediaryNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/TrafficStatus1> .
<https://example.com/MuxNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/DataMux1> .
<https://example.com/SuperNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/SuperLoad1> .

# Link hubs and high-degree nodes to a super node
<https://example.com/SuperNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/SuperNodeLoad> .
<https://example.com/HubNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/HubLoad1> .
<https://example.com/HighDegreeNode1> noria:structuralElementObservable <https://example.com/RouterLoad1> .

# Dismiss isolated nodes: all nodes are linked via observables or managedBy relations, ensuring no isolated nodes remain.